<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    
      <p>A system consists of two blocks, of masses m and 2m, attached to the ends of a spring with a force constant k. The system is placed on a horizontal frictionless surface. The blocks then are pulled an "extra" distance x apart and released from the state of rest. 
During the subsequent motion of the blocks, what is the maximum speed of block m? 

</p>
      <br/>
    
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11">
      <br/>
      
        <p>
Part 1. 

Which concepts are most useful in solving this problem?
</p>
      
      <part loncapaid="12">
        <br/>
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="13" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                  Conservation of energy and constant-acceleration kinematics
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                  Newton's laws and conservation of mechanical energy
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                  Conservation of momentum and constant-acceleration kinematics
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                  Conservation of mechanical energy and kinematics of simple harmonic motion
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="true">

                  Conservation of mechanical energy and conservation of momentum
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

                  Newton's laws and constant-acceleration kinematics
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil7" correct="false">

                  Conservation of momentum and kinematics of simple harmonic motion
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="14">
        
          <p>
Part 2. 
What condition is necessary in order for both mechanical energy and momentum of the spring-blocks system to be conserved? 
</p>
        
        <br/>
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="15" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">

                  The surface must be frictionless 
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">

                  The surface must be horizontal
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                  The spring must obey Hooke's law
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                  The masses of the blocks must be different from each other
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                  The forces exerted on the blocks by the spring must be proportional to their masses
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

                  The accelerations of the blocks must be equal
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="16">
        
          <p>
Part 3. 
At the moment when the speed of block m is at a maximum, what statement is true? 
</p>
        
        <br/>
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="17" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                  The speed of block 2m is zero 
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">

                  The speed of block 2m is at a maximum
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="true">

                  The net force acting on block m is zero
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="true">

                  The net force acting on block 2m is zero
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                  The elastic potential energy of the system is at a maximum
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="true">

                  The elastic potential energy of the system is zero
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil7" correct="false">

                  The center of mass of the system is moving in the same direction as block m
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil8" correct="false">

                  The center of mass of the system is moving in the same direction as block 2m
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="18">
        
          <p>
Part 4. 
If the maximum speed of block 2m is u, which equation is correct?
</p>
        
        <br/>
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="19" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">

                  k\(x^{2}\)

 = m\(v^{2}\) + 2m\(u^{2}\) 
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                  k\(x^{2}\)

 = m\(v^{2}\) - 2m\(u^{2}\)
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                  k\(x^{2}\)

 = -m\(v^{2}\) + 2m\(u^{2}\)
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                  k\(x^{2}\)

 = m\(v^{2}\)
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                  k\(x^{2}\)

 =  2m\(u^{2}\)
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

 m\(v^{2}\) = 2m\(u^{2}\)
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="20">
        
          <p>
Part 5. 
If the maximum speed of block 2m is u, which equation is correct?
</p>
        
        <br/>
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="21" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="true">

                  mv = 2mu 
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                  m/v = 2m/u
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                  2m/v = m/u
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                  mu = 2mv
                              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      
    </parameter>
  </problem>
</html>
